2
00:01:07,445 --> 00:01:09,948
I'm looking for Darby Reese.

3
00:01:11,157 --> 00:01:13,785
Does he know you're coming?

4
00:01:13,785 --> 00:01:15,912
No, he doesn't.

5
00:01:33,848 --> 00:01:35,558
Darby.

6
00:01:35,683 --> 00:01:38,060
Someone's mom's here to see you.

7
00:01:39,312 --> 00:01:41,439
Yeah, all right.

8
00:01:42,231 --> 00:01:44,984
All right. Yeah. Who'd you say you are?

9
00:01:45,026 --> 00:01:47,654
Margaret Hall.

10
00:01:48,989 --> 00:01:51,575
He'll be right down.

11
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:21,356
How about this?

12
00:02:21,439 --> 00:02:23,691
- Mother of Beau.
- Mr Reese.

13
00:02:23,691 --> 00:02:26,403
You're younger than I expected. Please, sit.

14
00:02:26,444 --> 00:02:29,239
I wantyou to stay away from my son.

15
00:02:31,074 --> 00:02:33,618
Does Beau know you're here?

16
00:04:47,132 --> 00:04:49,093
- Where are your sneakers?
- Don't know.

17
00:04:49,218 --> 00:04:51,429
Please find them. You'll catch a cold.

18
00:04:51,762 --> 00:04:54,307
Oh, Jack! I'm sorry.

19
00:04:54,307 --> 00:04:57,643
Margaret, where on earth
is that damned remote?

20
00:04:58,936 --> 00:05:03,399
I don't know. Broken, isn't it?
Didn't Dylan step on it last night?

21
00:05:03,441 --> 00:05:05,652
For the love of Pete.

22
00:05:05,693 --> 00:05:08,363
Try the one in the study. I think it'll work.

23
00:05:08,446 --> 00:05:11,491
- And where is Mr Dylan?
- He's in the driveway.

24
00:05:13,910 --> 00:05:14,578
Dylan.

25
00:05:24,755 --> 00:05:27,633
- Sweetheart, where's your brother?
- In the driveway.

26
00:05:27,633 --> 00:05:31,303
- I mean Beau.
- He took off in the boat.

27
00:05:31,303 --> 00:05:34,056
Mad about something. I don't know.

28
00:06:26,236 --> 00:06:28,279
Been gone a while, kiddo.

29
00:06:35,787 --> 00:06:39,708
- I went to Reno today.
- I know. He called.

30
00:06:41,335 --> 00:06:43,379
I'm going upstairs.

31
00:06:48,968 --> 00:06:51,637
May I come in?

32
00:06:54,849 --> 00:06:57,143
May I come in?

33
00:07:03,608 --> 00:07:06,736
- I need to talk to you.
- You talk to everybody lately.

34
00:07:06,736 --> 00:07:10,615
- Please don't be glib.
- Like I told you, he's my friend. That's all.

35
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:13,743
Well, he may not be the friend you think he is.

36
00:07:13,785 --> 00:07:16,246
He's just a guy, all right? Just a place.

37
00:07:16,330 --> 00:07:21,335
- You've got to talkto me about the drinking...
- I shouldn't have been driving. I'm sorry.

38
00:07:21,460 --> 00:07:24,004
You shouldn't have been
visiting nightclubs...

39
00:07:24,129 --> 00:07:25,798
- Are we through?
- No!

40
00:07:25,923 --> 00:07:28,843
You could have been killed in that accident.

41
00:07:33,014 --> 00:07:35,558
I know you're having difficulty...

42
00:07:38,686 --> 00:07:41,105
If you're having feelings...

43
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:46,820
I don't know what it is you think I feel, but
you're blowing this thing out of proportion.

44
00:07:51,366 --> 00:07:54,327
He offered to stay away from you.

45
00:07:55,912 --> 00:07:58,081
- What?
- For money.

46
00:07:58,206 --> 00:08:00,667
He said if I paid him, he'd stay away.

47
00:08:02,002 --> 00:08:04,213
$5,000.

48
00:08:07,216 --> 00:08:09,301
- I don't believe you.
- It's true.

49
00:08:09,510 --> 00:08:13,389
- He said you'd tell me things.
- Beau, stop. Would I lie to you?

50
00:08:14,098 --> 00:08:17,977
- Was Darby with you Friday night?
- Just let it go.

51
00:08:18,978 --> 00:08:22,106
- I don't want you seeing him.
- Do we have to talk about this now?

52
00:08:22,106 --> 00:08:26,903
I don't want you going into Reno. We can
put the music lessons on hold for a while.

53
00:08:27,153 --> 00:08:29,864
Margaret, it's Tom.

54
00:08:37,205 --> 00:08:40,334
Yes. Tom, it's Margaret.

55
00:08:41,877 --> 00:08:44,046
It's good to hear you, too.

56
00:08:44,838 --> 00:08:47,383
Everything's fine. We're all fine.

57
00:08:48,676 --> 00:08:50,553
What?

58
00:08:50,553 --> 00:08:52,680
I can't hear you.

59
00:08:53,389 --> 00:08:55,474
Yeah. Dylan's helping me.

60
00:08:56,642 --> 00:09:00,313
He's making Xs on the calendar.
Don't you disappoint him.

61
00:09:03,358 --> 00:09:05,235
Beau?

62
00:09:05,902 --> 00:09:08,488
Well, hold on a sec. He's right here.

63
00:09:13,326 --> 00:09:15,078
Hi.

64
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:17,789
I'm fine. Yeah, the same stuff.

65
00:09:17,831 --> 00:09:20,042
Yeah, school, water polo, you know.

66
00:09:20,584 --> 00:09:22,586
No, no. No answers yet.

67
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:25,339
Wesleyan lost my transcripts.

68
00:09:26,048 --> 00:09:27,841
Yeah.

69
00:09:27,967 --> 00:09:32,179
I'm not playing as much as I'd like,
but I'm enjoying the classes.

70
00:09:35,433 --> 00:09:37,643
No, the drive's been fine.

71
00:09:39,062 --> 00:09:40,063
I miss you, too.

72
00:10:35,912 --> 00:10:38,123
Are you crazy? That's my mother's room.

73
00:10:38,248 --> 00:10:41,001
- It's me.
- Yeah, I can see that.

74
00:10:41,126 --> 00:10:44,088
- You wanna have some fun?
- No!

75
00:10:44,171 --> 00:10:48,050
- Go away. You're gonna wake everyone up.
- Come on!

76
00:10:48,175 --> 00:10:50,845
Just go away. Someone's gonna see you.

77
00:10:50,886 --> 00:10:53,556
Hey, I came all the way from Reno.

78
00:10:54,515 --> 00:10:57,226
- Come on.
- All right.

79
00:10:58,102 --> 00:11:00,188
Quiet. Just be quiet.

80
00:11:00,188 --> 00:11:02,732
I'll be right down. Don't move.

81
00:12:04,963 --> 00:12:08,175
Make a sound,
I'm gonna drown you in the lake.

82
00:12:09,468 --> 00:12:11,554
Come on.

83
00:12:15,391 --> 00:12:17,685
Whatever you say, lover.

84
00:12:19,645 --> 00:12:21,814
Light a match or somethin'.

85
00:12:22,607 --> 00:12:24,859
Yeah. Much better.

86
00:12:28,238 --> 00:12:30,532
I'm sorry about my mother.

87
00:12:31,241 --> 00:12:34,494
I thought I was your little secret.
Imagine my surprise.

88
00:12:34,619 --> 00:12:37,205
She knew I was at the club
Friday night, that's all.

89
00:12:37,331 --> 00:12:40,584
- She doesn't really know...
- She knows, believe me.

90
00:12:41,919 --> 00:12:44,254
- Why are you saying that?
- Poor Beau.

91
00:12:44,421 --> 00:12:46,548
She's a mother, not a moron.

92
00:12:47,508 --> 00:12:49,301
Shut up.

93
00:12:50,094 --> 00:12:53,180
She was bound to find out.
That's the way things work.

94
00:12:53,306 --> 00:12:56,184
I just don't want you
talking to her any more, OK?

95
00:12:56,350 --> 00:12:58,269
- Or to anyone else.
- All right!

96
00:12:58,394 --> 00:13:01,522
No one. I'm serious. It's my business...

97
00:13:01,522 --> 00:13:03,816
Whatever you want, precious.

98
00:13:05,401 --> 00:13:08,947
What did you talk to her about?
What did you say to her?

99
00:13:09,239 --> 00:13:11,950
Nothing. Well, not much.

100
00:13:13,451 --> 00:13:16,121
You gotta relax, beauty.

101
00:13:16,246 --> 00:13:19,374
Why? What did she tell you?

102
00:13:20,375 --> 00:13:22,920
Did she ask you to stay away from me?

103
00:13:24,171 --> 00:13:26,757
- I believe she did.
- And?

104
00:13:27,508 --> 00:13:29,468
And I...

105
00:13:31,429 --> 00:13:33,597
All right, I...

106
00:13:34,515 --> 00:13:39,145
I told her I might be amenable
to a little negotiation.

107
00:13:39,228 --> 00:13:41,564
Friendly to an offer.

108
00:13:43,024 --> 00:13:45,151
Beau...

109
00:13:48,321 --> 00:13:50,907
To stop seeing me.

110
00:13:52,951 --> 00:13:54,953
Of course I was lying. You knowthat.

111
00:13:55,078 --> 00:13:58,957
I know what? Thatyou tried
to steal money from my mother?

112
00:13:59,124 --> 00:14:02,628
- It's only money. Don't take it so personally.
- Get off me.

113
00:14:02,711 --> 00:14:06,131
Look, I need money.
Haven't you noticed? I tend to overindulge.

114
00:14:06,298 --> 00:14:08,551
I said don't touch me.

115
00:14:16,225 --> 00:14:18,478
That hurt, you little fuck.

116
00:14:20,605 --> 00:14:22,690
Hey, come on, come on.

117
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:27,195
- Look, I'm sorry, all right? I'm sorry.
- Get off my arm.

118
00:14:27,278 --> 00:14:29,197
Beau, Beau...

119
00:14:44,588 --> 00:14:46,882
Jesus. You're not being a very good host.

120
00:14:46,924 --> 00:14:49,927
- Get out. Get outta here.
- Easy, tiger.

121
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:08,154
- Get the fuck outta here.
- That hurt.

122
00:15:18,874 --> 00:15:20,959
Beau, Beau, come on.

123
00:15:22,002 --> 00:15:22,920
Beau.

124
00:15:39,437 --> 00:15:41,439
Jesus, Beau.

125
00:15:50,782 --> 00:15:53,326
Beau!

126
00:15:53,326 --> 00:15:55,579
Sweetheart, what happened?

127
00:15:58,415 --> 00:16:00,125
Beau?

128
00:16:00,959 --> 00:16:03,796
I thought I was the only one up.

129
00:16:07,883 --> 00:16:11,470
- You're sure I shouldn't go?
- Yes, I'll be right back.

130
00:17:01,230 --> 00:17:03,900
- Problem?
- No, just the wind.

131
00:17:04,025 --> 00:17:06,653
Did I hear Beau earlier?

132
00:17:06,820 --> 00:17:10,115
No, I don't think so.
Why don't you get to bed? It's late.

133
00:17:22,044 --> 00:17:24,088
Margaret? Is thatyou?

134
00:17:25,297 --> 00:17:27,466
- You're up early.
- Trouble sleeping.

135
00:17:27,466 --> 00:17:29,927
- Going for a swim?
- Too cold.

136
00:17:30,344 --> 00:17:32,805
Just a walk. Maybe I'll run a little.

137
00:24:24,150 --> 00:24:27,570
Where have you been?
I lost my mitt. I can't find it.

138
00:24:27,695 --> 00:24:30,573
- It's around. We'll find it.
- Were you out in the boat?

139
00:24:30,699 --> 00:24:34,453
- Is Paige ready to go?
- You been AWOL quite a while, Maggie.

140
00:24:34,494 --> 00:24:37,789
- Did you look under your bed?
- I thoughtyou were out in the boat.

141
00:24:37,998 --> 00:24:41,585
Go look under your bed.
Paige, the Lloyds are here!

142
00:24:43,670 --> 00:24:46,382
- Is Beau up?
- Beau? No, I haven't seen him.

143
00:24:46,423 --> 00:24:49,260
So, you took a spin on the lake?

144
00:24:49,301 --> 00:24:51,345
Paige, slow down, please.

145
00:24:52,763 --> 00:24:55,516
- Hey, hey. Gangplank.
- Honey, the Lloyds are waiting.

146
00:24:55,683 --> 00:24:59,228
- Where were you all morning?
- Mom, I can't find it.

147
00:25:00,980 --> 00:25:03,858
Dylan, please. It's time to go - now.

148
00:25:04,984 --> 00:25:08,655
You'll just have to borrow a glove
from someone. It won't be so bad.

149
00:25:08,655 --> 00:25:11,157
- You can't just borrow a mitt.
- Course you can.

150
00:25:14,327 --> 00:25:16,580
Who's gonna let me borrowtheir mitt?

151
00:25:16,788 --> 00:25:20,250
You'll work it out, Dyl.
People like to share. Go on.

152
00:25:20,542 --> 00:25:23,337
- Running late?
- Yes, sorry. Lost track of the time.

153
00:25:23,337 --> 00:25:26,715
Do you mind picking up?
I have a tennis thing I can't get out of.

154
00:25:26,715 --> 00:25:29,677
- If you can't...
- No, I'll manage. It's not a problem.

155
00:25:29,802 --> 00:25:32,138
Great. Bye-bye.

156
00:30:19,812 --> 00:30:22,774
- What happened last night?
- Wesleyan wants another music sample.

157
00:30:23,066 --> 00:30:25,360
I'm being considered for a grant.

158
00:30:32,450 --> 00:30:34,870
I need $50 for the session.

159
00:30:36,872 --> 00:30:39,541
All right. So what happened last night?

160
00:30:39,541 --> 00:30:43,170
Can you give me a ride?
Cos I'm late for water polo already.

161
00:30:48,217 --> 00:30:50,052
Beau.

162
00:30:50,052 --> 00:30:52,847
What do you want me to say?
Thatyou were right?

163
00:30:52,847 --> 00:30:54,807
Fine. You were right, OK?

164
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:58,811
- I just wanna know what happened.
- Look, I'm already late.

165
00:30:59,020 --> 00:31:01,230
You're bruised and scraped.

166
00:31:01,230 --> 00:31:04,067
Something happened
and you've got to tell me...

167
00:31:04,108 --> 00:31:06,361
Oh, there you are!

168
00:31:08,947 --> 00:31:12,576
I thought we were gonna
take that skiff out for a spin.

169
00:31:12,701 --> 00:31:17,914
I just got back. Beau needs a ride to school.
Will you be all right for a little while?

170
00:31:17,998 --> 00:31:21,168
I was out on the dock.
I couldn't see you there.

171
00:31:22,002 --> 00:31:25,673
Found this, anyway.
On the beach in the sand, plain as day.

172
00:31:25,881 --> 00:31:28,926
I'm surprised you didn't see it
this morning on your walk.

173
00:31:28,968 --> 00:31:31,721
No. No, I didn't.

174
00:31:37,435 --> 00:31:39,562
What happened to your face?

175
00:32:00,209 --> 00:32:03,962
You're not gonna say anything to Dad?

176
00:32:05,172 --> 00:32:07,299
You know, about last night?

177
00:32:08,217 --> 00:32:10,511
No.

178
00:32:10,594 --> 00:32:14,223
All right. I'll find a ride back. Bye.

179
00:33:25,798 --> 00:33:29,176
I think boy ballerinas just don't look right.
They look so funny.

180
00:33:29,301 --> 00:33:31,387
I perfectly agree with you.

181
00:33:31,595 --> 00:33:34,890
You know, he put on
his tights the wrong way.

182
00:33:36,309 --> 00:33:38,519
I think it's very funny.

183
00:33:39,937 --> 00:33:44,150
Hey, are you sure you're not getting a crush?

184
00:33:44,734 --> 00:33:47,195
You know I was just kidding.

185
00:33:47,404 --> 00:33:49,531
Yeah.

186
00:33:50,782 --> 00:33:52,826
Hey, look!

187
00:33:52,951 --> 00:33:57,372
- What's going on? Did somebody drown?
- Keep movin'.

188
00:34:02,336 --> 00:34:05,798
Yes, I'm trying to get through
to Captain Thomas Hall.

189
00:34:08,634 --> 00:34:11,137
The USS Constellation.

190
00:34:19,228 --> 00:34:21,606
His wife Margaret.

191
00:34:21,773 --> 00:34:24,317
Please don't put me on hold again.

192
00:34:29,948 --> 00:34:32,617
I need to speakto him today. Right now.

193
00:34:34,536 --> 00:34:37,956
I realise they left port. I told you I'm his wife.

194
00:34:39,207 --> 00:34:41,877
Well, no, it's not exactly an emergency.

195
00:34:50,511 --> 00:34:52,763
His wife, Margaret.

196
00:35:01,606 --> 00:35:03,274
All right.

197
00:35:03,274 --> 00:35:05,777
No, no message. Thank you.

198
00:35:41,105 --> 00:35:43,524
He's dead.

199
00:35:44,484 --> 00:35:48,154
Darby's dead. He was killed Monday night.

200
00:35:48,279 --> 00:35:50,282
- That night he was here.
- Beau.

201
00:35:50,448 --> 00:35:52,617
It's in the paper. Look.

202
00:36:01,794 --> 00:36:05,464
- Did he know other people in Tahoe?
- How should I know?

203
00:36:05,464 --> 00:36:08,050
He knew everybody.

204
00:36:13,764 --> 00:36:18,186
The police are saying
someone murdered him.

205
00:36:18,186 --> 00:36:20,480
Did anybody else know he was coming?

206
00:36:21,397 --> 00:36:24,317
Did anybody know you were friends?

207
00:36:26,277 --> 00:36:28,655
Does it matter? Mom, he's dead!

208
00:36:28,780 --> 00:36:33,201
I don't know. Do you think
the police will want to speak with you?

209
00:36:35,912 --> 00:36:38,999
I don't know. I don't know.

210
00:36:46,757 --> 00:36:49,260
Must be a real relief to you though.

211
00:36:50,261 --> 00:36:52,430
- I mean, him being dead.
- Beau, please.

212
00:36:52,430 --> 00:36:55,600
That's gotta have some appeal.
Can't bother you, can't bother me.

213
00:36:55,725 --> 00:36:59,687
- Stop it, for Christ's sake.
- You know, you were right, Mom.

214
00:36:59,812 --> 00:37:02,690
He was a loser. Now it's just in the paper.

215
00:37:11,032 --> 00:37:16,121
Mom! There's a man downstairs.
He wanted to talkto Dad, but I told him...

216
00:37:16,163 --> 00:37:19,249
- Who'd he say he is?
- He didn't.

217
00:37:19,458 --> 00:37:21,793
All right, I'm coming.

218
00:37:31,554 --> 00:37:36,309
- Can I help you?
- Yeah. I came to see Tom Hall.

219
00:37:36,309 --> 00:37:40,396
- He isn't in.
- I can wait. I told that to the girl.

220
00:37:41,522 --> 00:37:43,524
I'm his wife.

221
00:37:43,566 --> 00:37:46,820
- When will he be back?
- He won't be. Not today.

222
00:37:48,530 --> 00:37:51,241
What exactly is ityou want?

223
00:37:54,035 --> 00:37:57,706
I came to talk about
Darby Reese and your son.

224
00:38:06,048 --> 00:38:08,050
Dylan.

225
00:38:08,175 --> 00:38:10,427
I need you to play somewhere else.

226
00:38:10,427 --> 00:38:13,055
- Why?
- I need to speak with this man.

227
00:38:15,182 --> 00:38:18,644
- Promise you won't touch the computer?
- Yes, I promise.

228
00:38:21,481 --> 00:38:24,025
I think you know Darby Reese.

229
00:38:25,235 --> 00:38:28,279
So, you must know he is dead.

230
00:38:30,031 --> 00:38:32,409
Murdered.

231
00:38:35,328 --> 00:38:39,625
Your son's been spending
a lot of time with Mr Reese.

232
00:38:40,125 --> 00:38:43,045
Special time. Sort of intimate.

233
00:38:43,629 --> 00:38:45,589
Forgot my fish book.

234
00:38:48,676 --> 00:38:52,138
Dyl, Dyl. No more interruptions.
You understand?

235
00:38:52,179 --> 00:38:54,140
Sorry.

236
00:39:00,063 --> 00:39:03,483
We know Darby was coming here
Monday night to see Beau.

237
00:39:04,817 --> 00:39:07,278
- The night he was killed.
- "We"?

238
00:39:07,404 --> 00:39:09,614
- Yeah, I have a partner.
- Partner?

239
00:39:10,782 --> 00:39:12,617
- Beau's done nothing wrong.
- Maybe.

240
00:39:12,742 --> 00:39:16,663
- I said he's done nothing wrong.
- So why haven't you gone to the police?

241
00:39:16,830 --> 00:39:20,459
- Why don't they know that your son and...
- Is there a point to this?

242
00:39:20,584 --> 00:39:24,171
We think your son is mixed up
in a murder. That's the point.

243
00:39:24,171 --> 00:39:26,256
I think you should go now.

244
00:39:26,423 --> 00:39:28,509
Have you been listening to me?

