Make somebody a great husband someday.

492
01:07:24,755 --> 01:07:27,049
- Can I help you?
- Hope so.

493
01:07:27,174 --> 01:07:31,011
Talkin' to the residents about the murder
at Buck's Cove. You heard about that?

494
01:07:31,262 --> 01:07:33,889
- OK, try it, and don't...
- I know.

495
01:07:36,017 --> 01:07:37,810
OK!

496
01:07:37,935 --> 01:07:40,063
Yes, we heard about it.

497
01:07:40,188 --> 01:07:43,900
Seems the victim was killed
with an anchor. Pierced his lungs.

498
01:07:43,900 --> 01:07:48,696
We were thinkin' maybe that anchor could've
come from one of these houses around here.

499
01:07:48,780 --> 01:07:53,410
Well, our dinghy doesn't have an anchor.
We tie it to the dock.

500
01:07:53,493 --> 01:07:56,204
- Always?
- Yes.

501
01:07:56,288 --> 01:07:58,707
All right. Like I said, just checkin'.

502
01:07:59,499 --> 01:08:02,461
If you think of anything, give us a call.

503
01:08:02,461 --> 01:08:04,546
OK.

504
01:08:10,427 --> 01:08:13,013
I'm stumped. What did he want?

505
01:08:14,223 --> 01:08:16,559
- You can't fix it?
- I don't know.

506
01:08:18,352 --> 01:08:22,190
No, I guess not. You probably
clogged the fuel lines.

507
01:08:22,649 --> 01:08:25,610
- You know, Beau's car...
- I'll call a taxi.

508
01:08:27,278 --> 01:08:31,491
- Where are you going, anyway?
- Some errands. I'll be back before dinner.

509
01:08:31,616 --> 01:08:35,454
- Well, how am I supposed to get to ballet?
- Sue's stopping by.

510
01:08:40,876 --> 01:08:43,045
7087 Lakeshore Court.

511
01:08:44,046 --> 01:08:46,131
Tahoe City.

512
01:08:48,467 --> 01:08:51,345
Yes. I'll wait outside. Thank you.

513
01:08:54,056 --> 01:08:56,559
You look nice. What's going on?

514
01:08:56,559 --> 01:08:59,020
Nothing. Just some errands in town.

515
01:08:59,937 --> 01:09:04,192
- You're taking a taxi?
- Yeah, the Jeep won't start.

516
01:09:04,234 --> 01:09:06,194
I could drive you.

517
01:09:07,237 --> 01:09:09,698
No, I'd prefer to be alone.

518
01:10:02,336 --> 01:10:05,089
You sure you wanna hock this stuff?.

519
01:10:05,756 --> 01:10:09,718
- Yes. How much do you think?
- I could go to 8500.

520
01:10:09,760 --> 01:10:12,430
Maybe 8600.

521
01:10:16,225 --> 01:10:19,645
Well, I was hoping
that you could give me more.

522
01:10:19,812 --> 01:10:22,315
8600 is more.

523
01:10:40,459 --> 01:10:42,586
Margaret, stop!

524
01:10:44,630 --> 01:10:47,633
- Where's your car?
- It wouldn't start.

525
01:10:47,758 --> 01:10:52,346
I don't have all the money. I could
only raise 12,000. A little more than 12.

526
01:10:52,388 --> 01:10:54,849
Here. Please say it's enough.

527
01:10:57,059 --> 01:11:01,606
- I need to talk to you. Just for a minute.
- Jack's waiting to be picked up. I'm late.

528
01:11:01,606 --> 01:11:04,108
- I'll drive you back to Tahoe.
- No, thank you.

529
01:11:04,359 --> 01:11:08,488
- Would you help me find a cab?
- I need to talk to you, please.

530
01:11:08,571 --> 01:11:10,657
Things have changed.

531
01:11:18,373 --> 01:11:20,751
The seat belt is above the door.

532
01:11:37,393 --> 01:11:40,062
- The hospital, not the house?
- Yes.

533
01:11:42,607 --> 01:11:45,193
No, thank you.

534
01:11:45,235 --> 01:11:47,904
I took you for a smoker.

535
01:11:54,995 --> 01:11:58,832
They arrested someone for Darby's murder.

536
01:11:59,666 --> 01:12:01,919
- That's impossible.
- It's more than possible.

537
01:12:02,044 --> 01:12:04,421
- Who is it?
- It doesn't matter.

538
01:12:04,463 --> 01:12:06,757
Who is it?

539
01:12:06,757 --> 01:12:09,510
His name is Donnelly. Martin Donnelly.

540
01:12:09,635 --> 01:12:12,596
- He didn't do it.
- Like I said, it doesn't matter.

541
01:12:12,596 --> 01:12:17,894
Nagle's lost the advantage, but he'll make
a deal with you. He'll wanna make a deal.

542
01:12:17,977 --> 01:12:20,730
Donnelly didn't kill Darby.

543
01:12:20,813 --> 01:12:22,065
- What?
- I know that.

544
01:12:22,065 --> 01:12:24,275
- You don't.
- I do.

545
01:12:24,317 --> 01:12:25,944
- How?
- It's not important.

546
01:12:25,944 --> 01:12:27,112
How?

547
01:12:38,415 --> 01:12:40,375
Darby...

548
01:12:41,668 --> 01:12:44,421
Darby came to our house
that night to see Beau.

549
01:12:49,510 --> 01:12:52,430
I had gone to his nightclub earlier in the day.

550
01:12:53,431 --> 01:12:57,518
Beau had been in a car accident.
He'd been drinking with Darby.

551
01:13:00,855 --> 01:13:03,942
You see... My husband...

552
01:13:05,777 --> 01:13:08,988
He won't understand as it is, his son being...

553
01:13:12,033 --> 01:13:14,870
I don't know howto talk to him about it.

554
01:13:16,371 --> 01:13:18,749
He's away at sea so often.

555
01:13:20,375 --> 01:13:22,544
It's not that...

556
01:13:27,424 --> 01:13:29,927
I must sound very silly to you.

557
01:13:34,140 --> 01:13:37,018
I just wanted him to stay away from Beau.

558
01:13:39,270 --> 01:13:41,564
But I failed.

559
01:13:42,690 --> 01:13:45,318
He came to the house that night.

560
01:13:45,485 --> 01:13:48,530
They fought in the boathouse.
I don't know why.

561
01:13:49,197 --> 01:13:52,993
I heard these noises and I came down.
Beau had run back in.

562
01:13:54,244 --> 01:13:56,163
I met Darby on the dock.

563
01:13:57,039 --> 01:14:01,210
We argued. I pushed him
and he fell through the railing.

564
01:14:01,335 --> 01:14:03,670
- You pushed him?
- Yes.

565
01:14:04,505 --> 01:14:05,297
And?

566
01:14:05,297 --> 01:14:09,385
The railing just gave way,
and he fell onto the anchor.

567
01:14:11,971 --> 01:14:14,890
- And I moved the body.
- You?

568
01:14:14,890 --> 01:14:17,101
Yes. In the boat, in the morning.

569
01:14:17,143 --> 01:14:19,729
- Alone?
- Of course alone.

570
01:14:19,937 --> 01:14:21,230
I don't believe you.

571
01:14:21,439 --> 01:14:25,318
I don't care what you believe.
It is what happened.

572
01:14:25,318 --> 01:14:28,571
- And I have to tell them.
- Tell them what?

573
01:14:28,571 --> 01:14:31,700
- That you killed a man?
- Yes.

574
01:14:31,700 --> 01:14:37,622
This is crazy. Whatever happened that night
is over. Done. It can't be undone.

575
01:14:37,831 --> 01:14:43,045
Not undone, but I can put an end to this,
to Nagle's threats, to all of this!

576
01:14:43,128 --> 01:14:45,798
Stop it! Just stop it!

577
01:14:50,261 --> 01:14:54,598
It's too late for that.
Whatever happened, it's too late.

578
01:14:58,895 --> 01:15:02,065
Listen to me. You have
your family to think about.

579
01:15:03,066 --> 01:15:05,652
The life of your family, not Donnelly.

580
01:15:06,528 --> 01:15:11,825
Forget all of this. Forget Donnelly,
forget Nagle and me.

581
01:15:12,534 --> 01:15:17,039
Go home. Put all this behind you
as if it never happened.

582
01:15:19,499 --> 01:15:22,044
Do you hear me, Margaret?

583
01:15:26,382 --> 01:15:28,592
Margaret...

584
01:15:41,272 --> 01:15:45,068
You've reached the Halls. Leave us your name
and number and we'll get back to you.

585
01:15:45,276 --> 01:15:47,529
Thanks for calling.

586
01:15:47,529 --> 01:15:51,866
Hi, it's Mom. I'm running late.
If the hospital calls, just...

587
01:15:53,743 --> 01:15:56,872
Never mind. I'll be home soon.

588
01:16:23,441 --> 01:16:27,987
Hi. I got a call that my grandfather
was waiting to be picked up.

589
01:16:28,571 --> 01:16:30,490
- Name?
- Jack Hall.

590
01:16:30,699 --> 01:16:33,827
My mother was supposed to
come and get him. Is he...?

591
01:16:35,745 --> 01:16:37,664
Great. Thanks.

592
01:16:37,706 --> 01:16:41,210
- Sure you don't wanna keep the wheelchair?
- Don't be ridiculous.

593
01:16:41,293 --> 01:16:44,171
It's bad enough they saddle me with this.

594
01:16:45,547 --> 01:16:48,050
This thing's a wreck.

595
01:16:49,260 --> 01:16:51,595
Can I take your cane? I can put it in the back.

596
01:16:51,595 --> 01:16:53,764
No.

597
01:17:11,157 --> 01:17:14,202
- How will you get home?
- I'll get a taxi.

598
01:17:34,974 --> 01:17:38,394
You know, I never thanked you
for your help with Jack.

599
01:17:39,228 --> 01:17:41,814
I was there, that's all.

600
01:17:41,939 --> 01:17:44,400
His heart had stopped.

601
01:17:45,902 --> 01:17:48,238
It happens.

602
01:18:17,894 --> 01:18:19,604
Nagle. It's Alek.

603
01:18:20,188 --> 01:18:26,236
I don't know. Columbia sent back my tapes,
and Wesleyan just asked for another one.

604
01:18:26,236 --> 01:18:29,280
- What about Annapolis?
- I didn't apply to Annapolis.

605
01:18:29,447 --> 01:18:32,242
Shame. It's a fine school.

606
01:18:33,493 --> 01:18:34,786
Just lie down.

607
01:18:36,329 --> 01:18:39,124
I think he was in 313.

608
01:18:39,207 --> 01:18:43,212
- You already told me that.
- Well, he can't have disappeared.

609
01:18:43,378 --> 01:18:45,756
Take a breath.

610
01:18:46,090 --> 01:18:48,300
He was checked out to a Beau Hall.

611
01:18:55,099 --> 01:18:57,560
It's time to stop this, that's all.

612
01:18:58,394 --> 01:19:00,813
She came up with 12. There is no more.

613
01:19:01,773 --> 01:19:05,735
No. The husband's on a boat somewhere.
It won't happen for him.

614
01:19:05,777 --> 01:19:08,321
We got what we could. Let it go now.

615
01:19:12,909 --> 01:19:15,245
Battleships.

616
01:19:15,370 --> 01:19:17,456
I never liked carriers.

617
01:19:17,497 --> 01:19:21,877
Who was the guy who used to give us
those helicopter rides, in Virginia?

618
01:19:22,085 --> 01:19:26,840
- No one ever gave you helicopter rides.
- Don't you remember? The tall guy?

619
01:19:27,758 --> 01:19:30,386
- That's hogwash.
- I'll be right back.

620
01:19:31,262 --> 01:19:34,890
And no helo rides. Not on my watch.

621
01:19:35,808 --> 01:19:38,644
So explain it to me again. Maybe I'm stupid.

622
01:19:39,270 --> 01:19:42,357
I already told you.
Donnelly will be out by tomorrow,

623
01:19:42,440 --> 01:19:44,525
in which case we have what we had all along.

624
01:19:44,901 --> 01:19:47,779
You got most of what you wanted.
It's over. It's enough.

625
01:19:47,862 --> 01:19:50,991
I don't want "most". I want "all".

626
01:19:51,116 --> 01:19:54,578
Why is it so hard for you to understand that?

627
01:19:54,578 --> 01:19:57,122
I'm warning you, Carlie. Don't be greedy.

628
01:19:57,122 --> 01:20:02,085
It's not your place to warn me.
You should know that. It's not your place!

629
01:20:02,836 --> 01:20:07,508
Jesus. What the hell is she doing
in a taxi in Tahoe?

630
01:20:09,176 --> 01:20:11,762
I asked you to handle this. You did not.

631
01:20:11,762 --> 01:20:16,183
I don't know why, I'm confused.
But I'm gonna do this now.

632
01:20:38,957 --> 01:20:42,127
- Who are you?
- I think you know my partner.

633
01:20:42,252 --> 01:20:44,755
Please go. I can't talkto you, not here.

634
01:20:44,797 --> 01:20:47,257
You'll talkto me.

635
01:21:12,200 --> 01:21:15,162
- What do you want?
- Just the money. I just want the money.

636
01:21:15,370 --> 01:21:18,999
- I gave it to Alek.
- Part. You gave him part. I don't want part.

637
01:21:19,041 --> 01:21:22,294
- He said that Donnelly...
- He didn't kill Darby. It's idiotic.

638
01:21:22,377 --> 01:21:26,382
- The police will know soon enough.
- Just get out of my house.

639
01:21:29,718 --> 01:21:33,556
This is the problem
and I would like to resolve it now.

640
01:21:34,056 --> 01:21:36,309
I'll try and be clear.

641
01:21:36,559 --> 01:21:39,812
I think you've lied to Al.
I think you've put ideas in his head.

642
01:21:39,812 --> 01:21:41,898
I think you have the money.

643
01:21:41,898 --> 01:21:46,736
I think you haven't been altogether
straight forward with us...

644
01:21:49,489 --> 01:21:51,825
if you wanna know the truth.

645
01:21:53,994 --> 01:21:56,371
What kind of a fool do you think I am?

646
01:21:58,165 --> 01:22:01,710
- Would I risk anything if I had the money?
- Maybe.

647
01:22:02,586 --> 01:22:04,505
Where's your husband?

648
01:22:04,713 --> 01:22:08,259
I'd like to talk with him, because
I don't want this going on any longer.

649
01:22:08,425 --> 01:22:11,971
I can't seem to get any kind of
straight answer from you.

650
01:22:13,389 --> 01:22:15,683
Carlie.

651
01:22:17,435 --> 01:22:20,062
Alek, go away.

652
01:22:20,188 --> 01:22:22,774
- Are you all right?
- Yes.

653
01:22:24,067 --> 01:22:28,154
- I told you not to come here.
- That was not your right.

654
01:22:28,154 --> 01:22:30,448
- You lost control.
- That's not important.

655
01:22:30,448 --> 01:22:34,119
Al, please. Please go. Go away.

656
01:22:34,202 --> 01:22:37,330
- This woman's made a fool of you.
- Think what you want.

657
01:22:37,330 --> 01:22:40,417
A stupid, stupid fool. A weakling.

658
01:22:40,459 --> 01:22:43,378
- You've behaved like a stupid weakling.
- Shut up.

659
01:22:43,420 --> 01:22:47,424
Are you fucking her? Is that what's going on?
Is that it? You're fucking her?

660
01:22:47,508 --> 01:22:50,511
- I said shut up.
- Don't talk to me that way.

661
01:22:55,600 --> 01:22:58,060
Get out of here.

662
01:22:58,060 --> 01:23:00,855
- Don't push this, Al.
- Get out!

663
01:23:27,675 --> 01:23:29,844
Alek.

664
01:23:35,433 --> 01:23:38,352
Alek, I...

665
01:24:05,881 --> 01:24:07,675
Alek...

666
01:24:07,675 --> 01:24:09,969
Be quiet.

667
01:24:10,052 --> 01:24:12,138
Please, I beg you, don't.

668
01:24:50,928 --> 01:24:53,389
I'll go to the police.

669
01:24:55,224 --> 01:25:00,313
I'll tell them about Darby. I'll tell them
you killed Nagle in self-defence.

670
01:25:03,524 --> 01:25:06,069
I'll go to the police, Alek.

671
01:25:06,194 --> 01:25:08,363
I'm sorry.

672
01:25:11,157 --> 01:25:13,827
It shouldn't have come to this.

673
01:25:23,837 --> 01:25:25,923
Alek, Alek...

674
01:25:25,923 --> 01:25:27,925
Alek...

675
01:25:31,178 --> 01:25:33,806
We have no choice now.

676
01:25:37,059 --> 01:25:40,062
Please... You gotta let me tell 'em.

677
01:25:42,774 --> 01:25:44,651
Please.

678
01:26:17,101 --> 01:26:19,562
Listen to me. Go inside.

679
01:26:20,313 --> 01:26:23,566
No one can be near the windows.
Think of something, anything.

680
01:26:23,733 --> 01:26:26,152
Just keep your family away.

681
01:26:26,194 --> 01:26:31,866
Meet me in the driveway. We'll go together.
Take my car keys. In my coat, on the right.

682
01:26:32,784 --> 01:26:35,328
I'll drive Nagle's car. You follow in mine.

683
01:26:35,537 --> 01:26:39,166
Butyou must go inside.
I'll wait in the driveway.

684
01:26:40,792 --> 01:26:43,337
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

685
01:27:36,183 --> 01:27:38,352
No.

686
01:27:38,686 --> 01:27:40,646
No...

687
01:27:56,288 --> 01:27:57,456
Mom?

688
01:28:02,920 --> 01:28:05,047
What's going on?

689
01:28:09,844 --> 01:28:13,889
- Your lip! Jesus...
- Beau, I need you to help me.

690
01:28:14,015 --> 01:28:18,227
- Where are you going?
- I can't drive this. The shift...

691
01:28:18,895 --> 01:28:22,315
- I need you to drive the car. Please.
- Mom...

692
01:28:22,482 --> 01:28:25,818
Please. We need to leave now.
Can you help me?

693
01:28:25,944 --> 01:28:28,321
Just... Please, just help me.

694
01:28:41,460 --> 01:28:45,005
It's a grey car. Did you see it in the driveway?

695
01:28:45,089 --> 01:28:46,924
No.

696
01:28:51,595 --> 01:28:53,973
There. Is that it?

697
01:29:08,488 --> 01:29:11,866
He shouldn't have left like that.
He should have waited.

698
01:29:19,416 --> 01:29:23,170
- It's not what you think.
- How do you know what I think?

699
01:29:23,921 --> 01:29:26,340
- He's a friend.
- Yeah.

700
01:29:29,885 --> 01:29:32,471
That's all. He's just a friend.

701
01:29:40,062 --> 01:29:42,607
Did you see that?

702
01:30:06,131 --> 01:30:08,801
Beau, Beau! Please, call for help.

703
01:30:13,639 --> 01:30:17,143
- Alek! Alek!
- You shouldn't have followed me.

704
01:30:17,143 --> 01:30:21,064
- Jesus! Jesus!
- Why did you follow me?

705
01:30:21,189 --> 01:30:23,691
You didn't wait. Why didn'tyou wait?

706
01:30:23,691 --> 01:30:28,196
I lost control of the car, Margaret. My arm.

707
01:30:29,030 --> 01:30:31,449
Margaret, stop. Stop!

708
01:30:34,452 --> 01:30:36,621
Margaret, stop.

709
01:30:37,456 --> 01:30:39,583
Stop!

710
01:30:41,752 --> 01:30:45,130
- I'm gonna get you out of here.
- No, no!

711
01:30:45,255 --> 01:30:47,508
Just leave.

712
01:30:47,591 --> 01:30:51,220
- Someone will come.
- Oh, Alek.

713
01:30:51,887 --> 01:30:55,224
They'll think he died here in the crash.

714
01:30:55,391 --> 01:30:58,477
- Please go.
- I can't leave you.

715
01:30:59,937 --> 01:31:03,232
Butyou must.
They can't find you here. Think!

716
01:31:04,734 --> 01:31:06,778
Please, no.

717
01:31:08,196 --> 01:31:13,076
Margaret, the tape and the money.

718
01:31:13,827 --> 01:31:16,580
Look for them.

719
01:31:16,621 --> 01:31:19,333
They were on the seat. Can you see them?

720
01:31:21,126 --> 01:31:23,462
Get them out.

721
01:31:35,725 --> 01:31:38,644
- I can't see where...
- Just try.

722
01:31:52,826 --> 01:31:55,370
- Now go.
- No, Alek.

723
01:32:01,543 --> 01:32:03,629
I can't.

724
01:32:04,630 --> 01:32:06,882
Please go.

725
01:32:18,769 --> 01:32:21,272
I'm sorry, Margaret.

726
01:32:22,565 --> 01:32:25,026
I'm sorry for all of this.

727
01:32:33,910 --> 01:32:36,079
Margaret...

728
01:32:38,999 --> 01:32:41,168
Yes?

729
01:32:43,629 --> 01:32:45,923
I think...

730
01:32:49,301 --> 01:32:51,470
I'm not...

731
01:33:00,396 --> 01:33:02,357
Alek...

732
01:34:52,596 --> 01:34:54,890
Mom?

733
01:35:09,364 --> 01:35:11,908
Do you want me to call somebody?

734
01:35:22,586 --> 01:35:24,755
